                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.214,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has the opinion of the Court in case 13-1487 Henderson v. United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.214,
                        "stop": 227.112,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.214,
                                "stop": 16.914,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Sometimes during the course of a criminal prosecution the federal government ends up with guns owned by the person who is accused of the crime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.914,
                                "stop": 22.802,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The police might take those guns during a search where the defendant might turn them over himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.802,
                                "stop": 34.674,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Either way if the defendant is convicted of a felony he won\u0027t be able to get the guns back because the federal statute prohibits convicted felons from possessing any firearms."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.674,
                                "stop": 45.908,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In this case petitioner Tony Henderson was charged with a drug crime and the judge required him to turn over his guns to the FBI as a condition of getting out on bail."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.908,
                                "stop": 50.198,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Henderson eventually pleaded guilty and served some time in prison."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.198,
                                "stop": 57.793,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When he was released he knew he couldn\u0027t get his guns back because of the statute that bans felons from possessing guns."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.793,
                                "stop": 65.602,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So he asked the FBI to transfer his guns to a friend who had agreed to buy them, but the FBI refused."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.602,
                                "stop": 84.182,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Henderson then asked the Federal District Court to order the FBI to transfer his guns, but both that Court and the Court of Appeals for the 11th Circuit refused too on the grounds that if they agreed to Henderson\u0027s request he would possess the guns in violation of Federal Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.182,
                                "stop": 89.587,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now to understand this case you have to realize that possession is a broad term in Federal Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.587,
                                "stop": 98.33,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It includes not just actual possession that is physical custody of a thing, but also something called constructive possession."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.33,
                                "stop": 107.546,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I have constructive possession over a thing when I can exercise control over it, even if someone else is physically holding it at the time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.546,
                                "stop": 120.529,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That means the firearm law at issue here prevents a felon not only from holding his guns himself, but also for maintaining control over those guns in the hands of others."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.529,
                                "stop": 131.528,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In this case the lower courts and the government thought that Henderson would have that kind of control simply by virtue of picking the person who would next receive the guns."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.528,
                                "stop": 144.553,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We had to decide whether that\u0027s right, does a felon control and therefore possess his firearms any time he asks the Court to transfer them to someone whom he is designated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.553,
                                "stop": 162.9,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We think not, in this situation a Court-supervised transfer of guns held by a federal agency a felon only has control over his guns if after the transfer is completed the felon will have the ability to use them or direct their use."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.9,
                                "stop": 167.241,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Designating the next recipient is not itself enough."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.241,
                                "stop": 176.63,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So for example, the Federal Law allows a felon to place his guns in a secure trust for distribution to his children after his death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.63,
                                "stop": 185.271,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "What it does not allow is a transfer to a person who would allow a felon to decide how the guns should be used in the future."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.271,
                                "stop": 196.932,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "One way to ensure that a transfer complies with Federal Law is to hand the guns over to a firearms dealer who can then sell them on the open market and give the felon the money from the sale."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.932,
                                "stop": 213.039,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But that is not the only option, a Court can also approve the transfer to a person who expects to keep the guns so long as the Court is satisfied that that person will not later allow the felon to use the guns or to influence their use."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 213.039,
                                "stop": 223.595,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Neither of the courts below apply these principles to Henderson\u0027s request so we vacate the judgment of the 11th Circuit and remand the case for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 223.595,
                                "stop": 227.112,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
